    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It sounds like you're saying the \"critics\" have a strong point about the uncertainty. If we're talking about a risk that could actually end humanity, isn't it objectively more responsible to prioritize the precautionary principle over the speculative benefits of speed? How can you weigh huge potential gains against the literal extinction of the species?",
